{
  "texts": [
    "Eilertsen et al.",
    "introduce an LLMpowered framework for intent-based classification of phishing emails, focusing on identifying attacker objectives rather than binary detection [Eilertsen et al., 2025].",
    "While their approach enriches threat intelligence analysis, it does not address emotional manipulation, paraphrasing robustness, or metadata cues.",
    "provide a broad survey of Bayesian, non-Bayesian, and deep learning approaches to phishing detection, outlining their strengths, limitations, and typical deployment challenges [Ige et al., 2024].",
    "As phishing attacks become increasingly AI-enhanced, studies have also examined the offensive capabilities of LLMs."
  ]
}